  <title>Working with Projects</title>

  <p>Projects store all your tracks and recordings together in a single folder.</p>

  <section id="new-project">
    <title>Creating a New Project</title>
    <steps>
      <item><p>Select <guiseq><gui>Menu</gui><gui>New Project</gui></guiseq> or press 
      <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>N</key></keyseq>.</p></item>
      <item><p>If you have unsaved changes, you'll be asked to save them first.</p></item>
      <item><p>A new project with one empty track is created.</p></item>
    </steps>
  </section>

  <section id="open-project">
    <title>Opening a Project</title>
    <steps>
      <item><p>Select <guiseq><gui>Menu</gui><gui>Open Project…</gui></guiseq> or press 
      <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>O</key></keyseq>.</p></item>
      <item><p>Navigate to your project folder and select the <file>.atr</file> file.</p></item>
      <item><p>All tracks and recordings are loaded.</p></item>
    </steps>
    <note style="tip">
      <p>The application automatically opens your most recent project when launched.</p>
    </note>
  </section>

  <section id="save-project">
    <title>Saving a Project</title>
    
    <p><gui style="button">Save Project</gui> (<keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>S</key></keyseq>):</p>
    <list>
      <item><p>Saves to the existing location if the project was previously saved.</p></item>
      <item><p>Prompts for a location if it's a new project.</p></item>
    </list>

    <p><gui style="button">Save Project As…</gui> (<keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>Shift</key><key>S</key></keyseq>):</p>
    <list>
      <item><p>Always prompts for a new location.</p></item>
      <item><p>Creates a copy of the project in the new location.</p></item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <section id="project-structure">
    <title>Project File Structure</title>
    <p>Each project is stored in a folder containing:</p>
    <list>
      <item><p><file>projectname.atr</file> — Project metadata file (JSON format)</p></item>
      <item><p><file>audio/</file> — Folder containing all track recordings as WAV files</p></item>
    </list>
    <note style="warning">
      <p>Keep the <file>.atr</file> file and <file>audio/</file> folder together. 
      Moving or deleting audio files will break the project.</p>
    </note>
  </section>

  <section id="unsaved-changes">
    <title>Unsaved Changes</title>
    <p>When closing the application or starting a new project with unsaved changes, 
    you'll be prompted to:</p>
    <list>
      <item><p><gui style="button">Save</gui> — Save the current project first</p></item>
      <item><p><gui style="button">Don't Save</gui> — Discard changes</p></item>
      <item><p><gui style="button">Cancel</gui> — Return to the application</p></item>
    </list>
  </section>

